<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Hale</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 7.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Mr. Perry’s despatch of September 19, No,
                            221, has been received. His proceedings in regard to the
                            misunderstanding which exists between Spain and Chili seem to me to have
                            been altogether judicious and discreet, and they are approved. We are
                            without any recent advices upon the subject from Chili. Our solicitude
                            about the affair continues unabated, and our good offices to serve peace
                            will not be remitted.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John</hi> P. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hale,</hi>
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Madrid.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>